<p>Khatami‚Äôs role in mobilising voters was celebrated by those who pointed to the fact he has faced severe restrictions on his movement and activities in recent years, <a class="u-underline" data-component="in-body-link" data-link-name="in body link" href="http://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/feb/17/iranian-media-banned-from-mentioning-mohammad-khatami">including a ban</a> on the Iranian media mentioning his name or publishing his photograph.</p>

<p>Khatami‚Äôs video also inspired a Telegram message that referenced the controversial frontrunner for the Republican nomination in the US presidential election.</p>

<p>In the joke, Iranian foreign minister Mohamamd Javad Zarif calls up his US counterpart John Kerry and says: ‚ÄúHey, man, if Donald Trump is really becoming a problem for you guys let me know. I‚Äôll tell our Mohammad [Khatami] to send a message.‚Äù</p>

